Adjust racks to middle and top positions and preheat oven to 400 degrees.

Line a #baking sheet{} with foil. Bring a large #pot{} of @salted water{} to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered) (quarter both lemons for 4 servings). Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Cut @Roma tomato{2}(cut into ½-inch-thick wedges).

Toss tomatoes on prepared baking sheet with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}; season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and half the @Tuscan Heat Spice{1/2%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest later). Arrange skin sides down. Roast on middle rack until slightly softened, ~{20-25%minutes}. Once tomatoes are done, remove from oven; heat broiler to high or oven to 500 degrees.

Once tomatoes have roasted about 10 minutes, remove @Italian pork sausage{9%ounce} from casing; discard casing. Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a medium, preferably ovenproof, pan (use a large pan for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add sausage; cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat and transfer to a #plate{}.

> TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

While sausage cooks, add @gnocchi{8.8%ounce} to pot of boiling water. Cook until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), then drain.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in pan used for sausage over medium heat. Add garlic and remaining Tuscan Heat Spice; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Add ½ cup reserved pasta cooking water (¾ cup for 4) and @chicken stock concentrate{1}. Bring to a simmer; whisk in @cream cheese{4%tablespoon} until fully incorporated. Stir in sausage, gnocchi, tomatoes, half the @Italian cheese blend{1/4%cup}, and @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) until combined. Add lemon zest and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, remaining Italian cheese, and a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer gnocchi now to a #baking dish{}.

Sprinkle panko mixture over gnocchi. Broil or bake on top rack until panko is golden brown and cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Divide between plates and serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.